                <section class="blog-section">
				    
                        <div class="large-blog-news single-blog-post single-blog wow fadeInUp animated" style="visibility: visible; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                            <figure class="img-holder">
                                <a href="/blog-article/blog/what-is-an-e-sim-and-how-does-it-work"><img src="/files/001196/gallery/articles/000001/w2sa-0-00-24.jpg" alt="News"></a>
                            </figure>
                            <div class="lower-content">
                                <h4 style="transition: all 300ms ease; font-size: 24px">What is an e SIM and how does it work?</h4>
                                <div class="post-meta">
                                   
                                        0 Comments
                                    
                                         |   2022-04-23 22:19:42
                                    
                                </div>
                                <div class="text">
                                     <p>We are all so used to the conventional chip embedded in a plastic card, which we all refer to as a SIM card. With everything going electronic and digital, our conventional SIM cards have also joined the bandwagon. ESIMs&nbsp;work just like your physical sim cards, just - they are embedded directly into your phone via software.&nbsp;</p><p>What does an eSIM look like?</p><p>An eSIM is basically a QR code, which you can scan using the option available on your device. (Check out the devices that support eSIMs below). Once you scan the QR code the eSIM is embedded into your phone via software. Walla! you have your international SIM card in your device without any hassles or extra costs.&nbsp;</p><p>Opting for the eSIM cuts out the trouble of standing in queues to get your physical SIM, or waiting for your physical SIM card to be delivered to your door (yes you can imagine the chaos&nbsp;if your delivery is messed up or late). You save on your costs of the physical SIM cards and more.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p><p>Before you plan your next travel, call in at our local Next360 office and inquire about eSIMs. It&#39;s time to go green and digital in travel as well!&nbsp;</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    
